
@startuml

' Define classes
class Employee {
  -name: String
  -socialSecurityNumber: String
}

class CreativeEmployee <|-- Employee
class Director <|-- CreativeEmployee
class Actor <|-- CreativeEmployee

class Technician <|-- Employee {
  -fieldOfActivity: String
}

class FilmSet {
  -location: String
}

class Film {
  -title: String
  -yearOfRelease: Integer
  -genre: String (Thriller, Action, Horror, Comedy)
}

class Screenwriter {
  -name: String
  -mostSuccessfulFilm: String
}

class Screenplay {
  -title: String
  -version: String
  -date: Date
  -numberOfScenes: Integer
  -plot: String
}

class Novel {
  -title: String
  -author: String
}

class Concept {
  -title: String
}

' Define associations
Employee "1" -- "0..*" Film : worksOn
Director "1" -- "1" Film : directs
Actor "0..*" -- "1" Film : actsIn
Technician "0..*" -- "1" Film : worksOn

FilmSet "1" -- "0..*" Film : usedFor
Screenwriter "1" -- "0..*" Screenplay : creates
Screenplay "1" -- "1" Film : basedOn
Screenplay "1" -- "1" (Novel or Concept) : basedOn

Director "1" -- "1" String : assistantName
Actor "1" -- "1" Boolean : hasOscar
Director "1" -- "1" Boolean : hasOscar

@enduml

---

### Explanation:

- **Employee** is the base class for all people involved.
- **CreativeEmployee** is a subclass of `Employee`, with **Director** and **Actor** as subclasses.
- **Technician** is another subclass of `Employee` with an additional attribute `fieldOfActivity`.
- **FilmSet** has a location and can be used by multiple films.
- **Film** has a title, year, genre, and is associated with film sets, directors, actors, and technicians.
- **Screenwriter** has a name and most successful film and creates screenplays.
- **Screenplay** includes details like title, version, date, scenes, plot, and is based on either a **Novel** or **Concept**.
- Associations:
  - A film is directed by one director, acted by many actors, and worked on by technicians.
  - A screenplay is written by exactly one screenwriter and used by exactly one film.
  - A film uses multiple film sets.
  - An actor and director may have an Oscar status.

